<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Position yourself across a flat bench, supporting your upper back while keeping your feet planted on the ground.</li>



<li>Hold a dumbbell above your chest with both hands, palms facing up, and lift your hips to form a bridge.</li>



<li>Lower the dumbbell in an arc behind your head, maintaining a slight bend in your elbows.</li>



<li>Engage your chest muscles to pull the weight back up to the starting position.</li>



<li>Repeat for the desired number of repetitions or check the guide below.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips </h4>



<ul>
<li>Maintain a slight bend in your elbows throughout the movement to enhance chest activation.</li>



<li>Bring the dumbbell past your head to feel a full muscle stretch (lats and pecs).</li>



<li>Keep your core and glutes engaged for stability during the exercise.</li>
</ul>



