<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Secure yourself on a decline bench set at a 15 or 30-degree angle below horizontal.</li>



<li>Hold dumbbells above your chest with palms facing each other.</li>



<li>Lower the weights in a wide arc until you feel a stretch across your chest.</li>



<li>Maintain control as you bring the dumbbells back up, focusing on your lower chest.</li>



<li>Squeeze your pecs together at the top of the movement.</li>



<li>Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, or check the reps and sets guide below.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Visualize hugging a barrel to guide the arcing motion of your arms.</li>



<li>Keep your chin tucked to maintain proper spinal alignment on the decline bench.</li>



<li>Experiment with different decline angles to find your optimal lower chest activation.</li>



<li>Focus on the quality of the stretch and contraction rather than the weight lifted.</li>



<li>Incorporate this exercise towards the end of your chest workout for maximum pump and definition.</li>
</ul>



